title: VEGOILS-Market factors to watch August 20
text:
The following factors are likely to influence Malaysian palm oil futures and other vegetable oil 
markets. 
FUNDAMENTALS 
* Malaysian palm oil futures eased 1.2 percent on Wednesday as weak crude and competitive 
vegetable oils weighed on prices of the tropical oil ahead of export data due out later this 
week. 
* U.S. soybean futures fell to multiyear lows on Wednesday in a broad-based commodities selloff 
and as widespread rains in the U.S. Midwest were expected to boost yields. 
* U.S. crude oil slumped over 4 percent on Wednesday to hit a 6-1/2-year low and almost break 
below $40 per barrel, as a huge unexpected stockpile build in the United States reinforced 
concerns about a growing global oil glut. 
MARKET NEWS 
* Fears about China's economy and falling oil prices kept world equity indexes under pressure on 
Wednesday, while the dollar lost ground after minutes from the U.S. Federal Reserve's July 
meeting left uncertainty over the timing of an interest rate hike.
